        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 3:15PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 315 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms across southern Washington County, moving east at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Landspouts, wind gusts up to 40 mph, and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible. Gusty winds
could knock down tree limbs and blow around unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Lindon, Anton, Last Chance and Cottonwood Valley.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
